In a surprise victory in President Obama's campaign to secure nuclear material worldwide, the Belarusian government announced Wednesday that it was giving up its highly enriched uranium stockpile, a critical component of nuclear weapons.
The agreement was announced in a joint statement issued after the security summit of Foreign Minister Hillary Rodham Clinton and Belarusian Foreign Minister Sergei Martynov.
For years, the U.S. government has tried to persuade Belarus to abandon its highly enriched uranium, and it seems that they hit a rock last spring.
