The year 2013 will mark the birth of a new currency zone, where countries that break the rules will be severely sanctioned and may be forced to declare deferred payments, and the private sector will also have to bear some of the costs.
Germany is suggesting that we must take a strong path of growth with increased savings and investment, moderate consumption, improved productivity and competitiveness, and capital reserves.
