The 60th parliamentary term was not yet started when the opposition bloc was formed in Congress, led by the members of the PRD (Partido de la Revolución Democrática), the PT (Partido del Trabajo), Convergencia (Czech "Covenant") and the independently declared Jesu Manuel Patrón Montalvo, and the four discussed one thing: the entry of "bipartism" into the Senate.
Before the start of the session for the 60th parliamentary term, Felipe Manzanarez Rodríguez of Convergencia, Ezequiel Reynoso Esparza of PT, Javier Corvera Quevedo of PRD and Patrón Montalvo "favored" the reform of the constitutional law because it excludes them.
This reform, they repeated, begins "bapartism", because now it will be two people from the same number of parties who will control Congress.
These four Members of Parliament, together with Gloria Margarita Santos Aquilar, the PRD Coordinator, were the only ones to vote against the Council, led by Salvador López Britt from the PAN (Partido Acción) and Luis Cardenas Fonseca as Vice-President.
Corvera Quevedo stated that these reforms constitute institutional political marginality at the urging of the PRI (Partido Revolucionario Institucional, Czech for 'Revolutionary Institutional Party') and the PAN.
He said that in the coming days they would talk to representatives of the PAN and PRI parties to modify the scheme based on political will, and if they do not have it, they would be subjected again by the two parties, ending the opposition coalition.
"When it's over, I'm watching it because we're excluded from any decision, and they're not even willing to consider the opinions of others".
Felipe Manzanarez Rodríguez of Convergencia stated that they agree with PRD, PT and Patrón and therefore will form a plurality group.
It is impossible to allow, he continued, that Congress, after being monopoly, is now "duopoly".
The aspiration of the law reform is not to have endless bipartisanism in Congress.
The group started with five lawmakers and its members are now talking to other colleagues to get more votes, Felipe Manzanarez Rodríguez added.
Ezequiel Reynoso Esparza of the PT explained that the Congress has now become "use" of two - in reference to the PAN and PRI parties.
"Once it was dominated by one party, now it is divided by two".
Patrón Montalvo asked for the respect of the personality of the MP to be given a seat at the table.
"So that the five of us, who are probably now nine, but they see us as five right now, not left out because of the covenants, each in a different faction, we have united to find a seat at the negotiating table, because the problem is that in the reform they have created and agreed to, we stand out, and we disagree with this reform".
